-- Heat Beat Thunder 100-96 to Tie NBA Finals at One Game Apiece
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2012-06-15T03:49:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-15/heat-beat-thunder-100-96-to-tie-nba-finals-at-one-game-apiece.html
The Miami Heat led from the start to
beat the  Oklahoma City  Thunder 100-96 and tie the National
Basketball Association Finals at one game apiece.  The Thunder, who trailed 27-15 after the first quarter and
78-67 at the end of the third, got within two points of the Heat
with 37 seconds remaining in the game.  After two meetings at Chesapeake Energy Arena in Oklahoma
City, the Heat will host the third and fourth games in the best-
of-seven series on June 17 and 19.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  